# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ALLOW-LIST .gitignore
#
# This directory holds PATIENT genomic data (PHI). To make it impossible to
# commit patient data by accident, we ignore EVERYTHING by default and then
# explicitly un-ignore only pipeline code + non-patient reference config.
#
# Never remove the leading "*" rule. To track a new code/config file, add an
# explicit "!<file>" exception below.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Ignore everything by default
*

# Pipeline code
!.gitignore
!README.md
!LICENSE
!filtering_r.pl
!parse_pangolin.pl
!run_filtering.sh
!vep_annotate.sh

# Non-patient reference / config
!g4e-2025.txt
!typevar.txt
!mane-plus-clinical-names.txt
!acmg_sf_v3.2.txt

# Explicitly DO NOT track (already covered by "*", listed here as documentation
# of what must never be committed):
#   *.vcf  *.vcf.gz  *.vcf.gz.tbi  *.tbi  *.bam  *.cram   <- patient sequence data
#   *.candidatos                                          <- patient results
#   *.pangolin.csv  *.pangolin.tsv  *.pangolin_input.csv  <- patient-derived
#   *_summary.html  *.log  vep.*                          <- run artifacts
